# Keep dev-paul's copy of unifier.md when merging from main.
# main never has this file; without this rule, git picks main's
# (empty / stale) copy and silently clobbers the full run history.
#
# `merge=ours` is NOT a git built-in driver — it requires a registered
# `merge.ours.driver`. `scripts/setup-git-merge-drivers.js` (run from the
# `prepare` lifecycle script on every install) configures it automatically:
#   git config merge.ours.driver true
# Run that command manually if you merge before installing dependencies.
docs/routines/unifier.md merge=ours
